    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;into wedges, keeping the peel on (this helps it cook quicker)</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>onion wedges</strong> to a baking tray, drizzle with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season them with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until they're tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
